2) How the two candidates map to those preferences/dislikes
- CD 2 (Warm, low‑compression analogue remaster): directly matches multiple core preferences — explicit warm, low‑compression analogue remastering; restoration of tape‑like transients and headroom; honest room imaging; LP‑style sequencing (concise front‑to‑back arc); intimate close‑miked center vocals and tightly blended harmonies; piano/organ and delicate acoustics with minimal overdubs; controlled bass/drums and a lyric‑forward, repeatable late‑night listening arc. Those attributes hit nearly every item on my preference list (warmth, tape transients, room, sequencing, vocal placement, minimal overdubs), and explicitly avoid the dislikes (no mention of crushed mastering, no bright AOR tightening, no anthology grab‑bag).
