In sum, while the careful remaster is attractive for its intimacy and low‑intervention mastering, the Organic Fleetwood Mac album aligns more closely with the decisive items in my stated tastes — piano‑forward dynamics, warm analogue midrange, upfront breathing female lead vocals, instrument separation, and album sequencing that rewards focused listening — and therefore is the better fit.

